### Code
```Rust
struct Foo {}

impl Foo {
    fn new() -> Foo {
        Foo {}
    }
    fn test() -> Foo {
        Foo::new()
    }
}

fn main() {}
```
At line `Foo::new()`, I expected the span of the hir `ty` in `QPath::TypeRelative(ty, ..)` to cover only `Foo`, but it covers the whole `QPath` `Foo::new` instead.

